<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-17T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-17T09:00:00-05:00" n="784" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d784">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">660m.6131/22: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SLA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-17T17:00:00+03:00">October
                                    17, 1939—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 17—2:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>762. The press today announces the signature on October 15th of a
                            Soviet-Lithuanian trade agreement for 1939–1940. The agreement was
                            signed by People’s Commissar for Foreign Trade <persName corresp="#p_MAI1">Mikoyan</persName> and the Lithuanian Minister in
                            Moscow and, according to the account published in the press, the
                            agreement between the two countries will provide for a total turnover of
                            40,000,000 lits, which will be almost double the present trade.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Kaunas.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>